                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_108158">Scalford, co. Leics</placeName>.

   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, prior</persName> &amp;c., of <orgName key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </orgName> grant that since <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> de <surname>Assheby</surname>
                        </persName> lately granted to a certain <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> de <surname>Bronage</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Bronage">
                           <forename>Mary</forename> his wife</persName> a messuage in <placeName key="place_108158">Scaldeford</placeName> called ‘Codyngton place’, which a certain <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> de <surname>Codyngton</surname>
                        </persName> once took from <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename>, prior of <orgName role="prior" key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </orgName>
                        </persName>, from
<pb n="110"/>
Monday after Easter 17 Ed. III [14 April 1343] for 60 years, the said Hugh and Mary shall hold it for the remainder of that term and for a further 10 years. Rent: 1/6. Given at <placeName role="date" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName>.
   <origDate when="1393-07-24">
                           <supplied>24 July 1393.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
